column5: We are headed for whitefish lake in Nolalu ontario from July 22-29. Walleye, perch, bass and northern. Headed there for our 9th year. Good luck to everyone in 2023.
Dang that is sweet. Midnight Sun - If the water level cooperates you will be ruined from fishing pike anywhere else! Tazan in July is prime time for big Trout! Very Nice! Brett

Held back on the other two trips while I get stuff organized. Working towards Taltson or Marshland in July Back to God's River to wear out my shoulder on Lakers and hopefully find a few more Brookies:-) Thanks!

Otatakan in June Rod for our group. We'll try to leave some fish for you to catch. Will be the 28th trip with Pickerel Arm Camps- only missed the 2020 covid year. Hoping to go back in the fall as well somewhere- enjoyed the weather and fishing in fall of 2021.
Leave some fish and some hundred dollar bills in the cabin pls,thanks Dan,

He only has the one lake. It is called Burnett not too far from Misekumaw. Same Cabins / Same Boats / same lake...just some weeks are guided and some are not. Cabins are new. Boats look really good. Picture of Misekumaw / Burnett / Misaw attached. Note there are two Burnetts in SK I believe. This one is furthest north. Misekumaw farthest West. Burnett furthest East. Misaw furthest north in the picture. Brett

Nice, thanks! The website stated "2 large bodies of water", so I assumed 2 different lakes.edit: I think this is it:59.064765, -102.319236I know the place now, I thought it sounded familiar. I thought you can access both Hara and Kingston? Looks like it anyway.Did you consider Misaw Lake Lodge as well?sorry to derail the thread..

Yes. Burnett is a huge watershed. It you look closely there a several lakes connected. I think some might be fly-outs for Hatchett Lake Lodge or Scott. Anyway I would love to have a shot at Burnett. Super good looking water. Brett

We're heading up to fish Cedar Lake next September. it will be our first trip to Cedar. We're really looking forward to fishing a lake with multi-species (walleye, pike, smallmouth bass, musky, and crappie) as we've previously fished lakes with primarily only walleye and pike.
